Dear All,=0A=
=0A=
Just a few remarks:=0A=
=0A=
Grothendieck was always very careful with terminology.=0A=
The name "topos" is an explicit reference to the idea of space.=0A=
The notion of geometric morphism between toposes is=0A=
taken from the notion of continuous maps between topological spaces.=0A=
=0A=
The idea of an "elementary topos" is a child of categorical logic,=0A=
especially of the axiomatisation of the category of sets by Lawvere.=0A=
The natural notion of morphism between elementary toposes is that of logica=
l functor.=0A=
=0A=
It is marvelous that the two notions should be so related.=0A=
But it is be better to keep them appart before uniting them.=0A=
Otherwise the miracle disappear in confusion.=0A=
=0A=
  =0A=
Best,=0A=
Andr=E9=0A=
=0A=
